lore.forestcraft.beequeen: Dangerous mob that can kill even a well-prepared player. With her huge sting, she is capable of dealing a lot of damage. She can also set any nearby bees on the player. You can summon by breaking a huge hive that spawns on the plains and in the flower forests.
lore.forestcraft.dandelioneer: Cute forest dweller who poses no threat to living creatures. It can be fed with a dandelion and propagated in this way. The fluff obtained from it is very soft, and the block made of this fluff fully protects against fall damage. It will spawn in small flower hills that generate in the forest.
lore.forestcraft.bakudan: A little demon who loves to play dodgeball. Spawns in a warped forest in the Nether. Having chosen it's target, the bakudan begins to run away from it, while trying to throw its charge. Often, valuable items can be found in their lairs. Bakudan's lairs can be broken with their own weapon.
lore.forestcraft.deer: A shy animal that can be bred with blueberries. After receiving enough damage, the deer stops running and is even able to hit you with its antlers. Spawns in a dark forest and snowy tundra.
lore.forestcraft.eater_of_the_depths: A sea monster that loves to hunt players and squids. If he chose you as his target, he will begin to circle nearby, periodically imposing blindness and weakness, making jerks in your direction. After being killed in your world, aquamarine begins to generate in the sea. It rarely spawns in the depths of the oceans.
lore.forestcraft.gem_golem: A neutral mob that spawns on Pearlstone blocks if they are deep enough underground. Able to deliver a lot of problems to those who decide to attack him.
lore.forestcraft.crocus_flower: If you do not approach this plant, then nothing bad will happen, but as soon as it senses the player next to it, it will begin to spew petals into the air, which can prevent the victim from escaping by causing Sleeping. Spawns in the jungle.
lore.forestcraft.petrified_runestone_zom: These ancient creatures were once sealed in ancient rune temples. They are very slow, but extremely tenacious. Very rarely, a key drops from them, allowing you to get the treasures of the temple.
lore.forestcraft.infected_zombie: Most likely, these zombies somehow entered into a symbiotic relationship with the Sporum mushroom. They are extremely poisonous and will leave a cloud of toxic spores upon death. They spawn in swamps at night.
lore.forestcraft.ancient_runestone_hero: The lord of the ancient rune temple is a formidable foe. The inexplicable power that he possesses allows him to manipulate the time of day, depending on which he will change his characteristics. Can be summoned with the Equinox Totem.
lore.forestcraft.insane_dog: It is not known exactly why these dogs are so different from wolves. If the insane dog gets close enough to you, it is capable of releasing redstone-breath that eats away at living tissue. They cannot be tamed, but you can force them to recognize you as a leader using the Insane Helmet. They spawns in bone lairs in the desert.
lore.forestcraft.alpha_insane_dog: These insane dogs are the leaders among the common. All nearby insane dogs will follow and hunt together. This mob is extremely dangerous and capable of handling a reckless target. There is probably something more terrible behind them, which is the reason for the appearance of these dogs. They spawns in bone lairs in the desert.
lore.forestcraft.insane_dog_overlord: A terrible creature that can destroy even an experienced warrior. It exudes terror, and from its appearance you unwittingly want to escape as far as possible. Most likely it is the reason for the appearance of insane dogs. Can be summoned with the Seal of Insanity.
lore.forestcraft.iguana_king: If you come across a large nest with an egg in the jungle, I advise you not to touch it, otherwise you risk being killed. The Iguana King is an extremely aggressive mob that can break blocks with its strikes. Are there regular iguanas in this mod? No, but maybe everything will change.
lore.forestcraft.thunder_screamer: When the sky is covered with clouds, and lightning strikes constantly nearby, there is a chance to meet this strange creature. It will not touch the player first, but if provoked, you can say goodbye to life. The electric shocks of these creatures are extremely deadly, but you can still make Electresistance Potion.
lore.forestcraft.terror_bringer: These huge birds that appear on the plains are extremely fond of eating meat. That is why they are a huge danger for pets rather than for the player. This does not mean that they cannot kill you. If you want such a bird for yourself, the way to its heart is through ...? The correct answer is meat!
lore.forestcraft.night_watcher: Sometimes it seems like someone is watching you. What if it doesn't really seem like it's better to leave the house and check. These creatures appear when you decide to lie down to sleep again. They will not touch you, but you woun't be able to sleep in their presence. This is a creature of the end and also can teleport, only not itself but you.
lore.forestcraft.cicada: Once again, walking through the forest, you can hear the chirping of cicadas. You have 2 options: Hate them or love them.
lore.forestcraft.krock: Kroks, once again prove that for a successful life it is enough to be prickly and be able to twirl. Very curious items can be made from their thorns. Spawns in the mesa (wastelands).
lore.forestcraft.soul_blaze: A rarer variation of Blaze. There are no special differences, but the drop from it can be used for extremely useful things. It spawns in the same way as Blaze.
lore.forestcraft.air_sucker: Always watch out for those who swim under your feet, because there is a high probability that this someone will want to sit on your head and start breathing through your lungs. These disgusting creatures will spawn in the deep oceans.
lore.forestcraft.wood_abomination: This hostile mob spawns at night in a dark forest. They make extremely strange sounds that can scare an expectant traveler. They do not cause any particular problem, but they try to attack with jerks.
lore.forestcraft.kelpy: The cutest creature, most likely it is a hybrid of kelp and fish. Spawns in the oceans.
lore.forestcraft.night_bat: Did you think that bats can only be friendly? No matter how it is! This mob will try to suck all the blood out of you as quickly as possible. A flock of these bats is hard to fight, even with good weapons. They spawns at night and in the caves.
lore.forestcraft.nether_bat: Very dangerous creatures. With big pack they can chase you to death.
block.forestcraft.cosmic_beacon.height_e: The Cosmic Beacon can only operate at an altitude above 150.
block.forestcraft.cosmic_beacon.time_err: The Cosmic Beacon only works at night.
